						<summary>

						<p>On the arch-stone of the entrance to Kṛishṇamūrti temple.</p>						

						<p>1788 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Plavaṅga, Mārgaśira ba. 14, Monday. On palaeographical grounds the record may be assigned approximately to the 18th century in which case the details may be equated to 1788 A.D., January 7.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of the Vēṇugōpāla temple by Aiyapa, the <hi rend="italic">Pēṭī Kotawāla</hi> of the Gājēndragaḍ fort. The inscription is in Nāgari characters and Kannaḍa language.</p>						

						</summary>
